{
  "stem": "17526.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 112.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, we could tell like clockwork a-- a reconnaissance plane we would see in the air.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Germans tried to shoot them down, and they would leave down these-- these aluminum foils to-- to camouflage it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we knew exactly that a day or two later, there will be a bombardment.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as soon we saw them, we knew the next day it's gonna be a bombardment.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there sure was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they had all kinds of smoke screens to blacken the-- the whole plant.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The plant was tremendous big.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one time I-- the Jews were not allowed in the bunkers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans and the prisoners of war were allowed in the bunkers, we were not.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One time I was running and the plane was right-- right above me, and I was trying to beat the plane and a bomb fell not far away.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from the crater it created, I was knocked down and I was covered up to my head in-- in sand and I dug myself out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Had I been a few feet closer to the crater, I would have been dead.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And later on towards the end, they did let us in in the bunkers for some reason.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At first, we couldn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "These were very reinforced heavy cement, five-foot deep bunkers with these round things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were all over the plant for the Germans, for the guards.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And one time, I was on one of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They let us in and this bunk took a-- this took a direct hit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I'll never forget-- never forget the trembling sensation, the fears.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The-- the-- the fear and the trembling, the whole-- the whole world was trembling and the noise.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
